#: 21337012-0-1406
msgctxt "21337012-0-1406"
msgid ""
"I despair of ever finding a solution to the catalyst problem. Even Zur's "
"usual unfounded optimism cannot seem to lift my spirits. I have gone over "
"all possible candidates for a catalyst to ignite the process to forge the "
"antipodal rods. The only substance that we might have access to is the "
"corrupted blood of a feral creature.\n"
"\n"
"We examined a dead creature and Zur tried to transform its blood, but his "
"alchemical process was flawed. Our Daedric captors, however, apparently had "
"more success in this area. Samples of corrupted blood are stored in the "
"experiment chamber, where they are guarded by a monster the Daedra created "
"using that very same blood.\n"
"\n"
"Now you comprehend my despair. If I had enough strength to access my full "
"power, I could easily subdue this monster and we could take as many vials of "
"corrupted blood as we could carry. As it is, we barely have the energy to "
"cast simple illusions, and even these fail more often than not. There is no "
"way we could survive an encounter with the chamber's guardian.\n"
"\n"
"Zur firmly holds to the hope that someone will find us. But I suspect that "
"our Mages Guild companions are busy dealing with their own problems.\n"
"\n"
"I fear this mission has already ended in failure and that we are doomed to "
"succumb to this soul-meld. But I shall not dash Zur's hope. As disorganized "
"as he can be, I find some small comfort in his blind faith."
msgstr ""
"나는 촉매 문제의 해결책을 찾는 것에 대한 희망을 거의 잃었다. 늘 있던 절의 근거없는 낙관주의조차 내 기분을 좋아지게 하지 못하는 것 "
"같다. 나는 대척 막대를 단조하는 과정에 불을 붙일 촉매에 쓰일 수 있는 후보들을 전부 검토해 보았다. 우리가 얻을 수 있는 유일한 "
"물질은 야생을 배회하는 생명체의 타락한 피 뿐이다.\n"
"\n"
"우리는 죽은 생명체를 조사해 보았고 절이 그 피를 변화시키려 해 보았지만, 그의 연금술 절차에 결함이 있었다. 하지만 우리를 붙잡은 "
"데이드릭 억류자들은 이 지역에서 더 큰 성공을 거둔 것 같다. 타락한 피의 견본이 실험실에 보관되어 있는 것이다. 실험실은 그 피를 "
"이용해 만들어낸 데이드라 괴물이 지키고 있다.\n"
"\n"
"이제 내 절망을 이해할 수 있을 것이다. 만약 내 전력을 다할 수 있을 정도의 힘이 있었더라면, 손쉽게 이 괴물을 제압하고 타락한 피를 "
"최대한 많이 챙겼을 것이다. 현 상황에서는 간단한 환영 주문을 간신히 사용할 정도의 힘만 남아있을 뿐이며, 심지어 자주 실패하기도 한다. "
"실험실의 경비와 마주치면 살아남을 가능성은 없다.\n"
"\n"
"절은 누군가 우릴 찾아올 것이라는 희망을 확고하게 가지고 있다. 하지만 우리 메이지 길드 동료들은 각자의 문제를 처리하느라 바쁠 것이다.\n"
"\n"
"이 임무가 이미 실패로 끝났고 우리가 이 영혼-융합에 굴복할 운명은 아닌지 두렵다. 하지만 절의 희망을 내동댕이치지는 않을 것이다. "
"절처럼 혼란스럽게, 난 그의 맹목적인 믿음에서 작은 편안함을 느낀다."

#: 51188213-0-1406
msgctxt "51188213-0-1406"
msgid "Catalyst Notes"
msgstr "촉매 기록"

#: 21337012-0-1401
msgctxt "21337012-0-1401"
msgid ""
"After all this time we may have found it.\n"
"\n"
"I wrote my husband several days ago to say that I may now know where the "
"Guardian's Eye is, and he showed up this evening with, of course, his band "
"of hooligan \"\"researchers.\"\" That lot came with salted meats and wine to "
"\"\"celebrate.\"\"\n"
"\n"
"The team is elated for the interruption, but we haven't found the Eye yet.\n"
"\n"
"Dear husband Quintus doesn't seem to understand this and insisted that I "
"tell him all I know of the Guardian's Eye, Volenfell, and its location. I "
"don't like the look of his merry band. Always whispering to each other in "
"the corner. It's a shame, but I don't trust my husband. I'll need the labor "
"he provides, though.\n"
"\n"
"I'm exhausted. Haven't slept in days. My team needs a good meal and a good "
"night's sleep, and so do I.\n"
"\n"
"I've left the Volenfell location with this entry in case you're reading "
"this, Abnaf. Yes, I know you read my journal, you eccentric misfit. And I "
"know you'll be too drunk tomorrow to keep up with the team at dawn. Follow "
"as you can."
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-1401
msgctxt "51188213-0-1401"
msgid "Tharayya's Journal, Entry 19"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-1400
msgctxt "21337012-0-1400"
msgid ""
"Dwemer records I've found might be able to help us locate Volenfell's actual "
"location. If that was not luck enough, rumor has reached my team that "
"unexplored Dwemer ruins may have been unearthed by changing winds here in "
"the desert.\n"
"\n"
"If these new ruins match up with my records, we may yet find the Guardian's "
"Eye."
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-1400
msgctxt "51188213-0-1400"
msgid "Tharayya's Journal, Entry 16"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-1399
msgctxt "21337012-0-1399"
msgid ""
"The swelling in my ankle has finally started to go away. Tripped on an "
"inactive Dwemer construct the other day. I kicked it, seeking revenge. It "
"didn't help.\n"
"\n"
"But my team's hard work is finally starting to pay off.\n"
"\n"
"It's an obscure lead, but it's the best one we have. It seems the Guardian's "
"Eye only took a brief respite here before making its way to another local "
"ruin: Yldzuun."
msgstr ""
"삐었던 발목이 드디어 회복됐다. 다른 날에는 정지한 드웨머 구성체에 발이 걸렸었다. 난 복수를 할 겸 그걸 걷어차줬다. 도움은 되지 "
"않았지만.\n"
"\n"
"그래도 우리의 정성스런 노력이 드디어 결실을 맺고 있다.\n"
"\n"
"모호한 단서이기는 하지만, 우리가 가진 것 중에서는 최고의 단서이다. 수호자의 눈은 이 지역의 다른 유적으로 보내지기 전에 아주 잠깐 "
"동안만 머물렀던 모양이다. 일드준 말이다."

#: 51188213-0-1399
msgctxt "51188213-0-1399"
msgid "Tharayyas' Journal, Entry 10"
msgstr "타라야의 일지, 항목 10"

#: 21337012-0-1396
msgctxt "21337012-0-1396"
msgid ""
"Though some of the initial excitement has faded, we're still confident we're "
"closer to finding the Guardian's Eye than any Dwemer researchers before us. "
"I would kill to get my hands on an ancient artifact of that repute. But I'm "
"better at research, honestly.\n"
"\n"
"There was a setback today. As far as I can make out, one of the old Dwemer "
"logs indicates the Eye was here only briefly to be worked on (the logs "
"mention some sort of maintenance or cleaning), and then was transported to "
"another Dwemer mine.\n"
"\n"
"As near as I can tell, the ruins referenced are those of Aldunz."
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-1396
msgctxt "51188213-0-1396"
msgid "Tharayya's Journal, Entry 2"
msgstr "타라야의 일지, 항목 2"

#: 21337012-0-1379
msgctxt "21337012-0-1379"
msgid ""
"… so the Ayleids saw the error of their ways. They buried the weapon deep "
